summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeGive BackNYX Professional Makeup Buttermelt Highlighter delivers butta boomin' glow! With high impact pearl that melts right in for butta'd up skin.
details: DetailsFeaturesButta smooth shimmers blend like powder and glide like butta.Transfer and fade resistant up to 12h wear with no falloutWith high impact pearl that melts right in for butta'd up skin. These smooth shimmers are buildable and buttery soft for a seamless glowTop it off with a multi-chrome topper shade for a butta glitz.Infused with mango butter, shea butter, and almond butter for a creamy texture that spreads like butta and wears for up to 12 hoursUsing a small, loose face brush, lightly spread onto the highpoints of your cheek, cupid's bow, collarbones and shoulders.Buttermelt highlighter spreads seamlessly over buttermelt blushVegan and always cruelty freeKey IngredientsShea, almond, and mango buttersItem 2638450How To UseGet ready for a butta glow. Using a small, loose face brush, lightly spread onto the highpoints of your cheek, cupid's bow, collarbones & shoulders. Even pop it on your brow bone, inner corner, & nose bridge for extra dimension. It's buildable and butta soft and works even betta when paired with buttermelt blush. reviews.headline: Hard to open
reviews.comments:
Let me start by saying that I'm a huge NYX fan.  I'd say about half of the makeup I own is NYX. I always check them first when I need something new. 
I had seen a lot of great reviews on YouTube and Instagram of this highlighter, so I decided to try it for myself in store. Most of the shades were sold out at my Ulta, which i took as a good sign that a lot of people like it. However, the testers were so hard to open just to swatch. I don't have very long nails and i could not open half of them. 
I did end up buying Butta Mint because it was in stock and i love the color. A mint highlighter is pretty unusual! But it's gorgeous in person. The highlight is stunning and not too green on. Its just more of a fun iridescent highlight. The product smells like coconut, which reminds me of sunscreen (in a good way).
When i got it home, I actually had to use a tiny flat head screwdriver to pry it open. I hope it will loosen up with use. If not, I am going to have to leave it open, which will likely make it go bad sooner. 
NYX, please do better with your components.

reviews.headline: Nice product, truly horrible packaging
reviews.comments: This gives a nice subtle shimmer, and I like how it feels, so I'll keep it. However, I honestly almost returned it because i.could.not.open.it. I find all of the Buttermelt line is difficult to open, but this one takes the cake. In fairness, I have arthritis in my hands and sometimes trouble open things. But even my 22-year-old daughter was unable to open this. I finally found success by using a scissors to pry it open. But unlike the other products in this line, it does not seem to be getting easier to open, so I've gotten to the point where I just don't fully click it shut. When I accidentally forget and shut it fully, I have to use the scissors again the next time I need to open it. I really don't know what they are thinking with this product packaging. Do better, NYX.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I finally got my hands on the Nyx Butter Melt Highlighter, and let's just sayI had high hopes. A creamy, melt-into-your-skin formula? Sounds like a dream. But does it live up to the hype? Let's break it down.

Formula & Texture

True to its name, this highlighter has a buttery texture. It's a hybrid between a cream and a powder, giving that smooth, almost mousse-like feel when you swipe it. It melts into the skin beautifully, blending with minimal effort. No chunky glitter, no chalky finishjust a soft, luminous glow.

Pigmentation & Finish

If you love a natural, dewy look, you'll be into this. It gives a radiant sheen rather than an intense, blinding highlight. You can build it up, but it's more of a lit-from-within glow rather than a metallic shine. If you're a fan of the Glossier Haloscope or Rare Beauty's highlighter, this might be up your alley.

Application & Wear Time

Finger application works bestbrushes don't pick up the product as well. It blends seamlessly over bare skin or foundation but can sometimes lift base products if you overwork it. Wear time is decent (about 56 hours before fading), but on oily skin, it might not last all day.

Shades & Versatility

Nyx offers a few shades, catering to different skin tones. The shade range is pretty but limitedI wish there were deeper, richer tones for more inclusivity. It's versatile enough to use on the cheekbones, brow bone, and even eyelids for a soft shimmer.

Final Verdict

Pros:
 Smooth, creamy formula
 Natural, dewy glow
 No chunky glitter
 Easy to blend

Cons:
 Can fade after a few hours
 Might lift foundation if not applied carefully

If you love subtle, everyday radiance, the Nyx Butter Melt Highlighter is a great affordable option. But if you're looking for an intense, long-lasting glow, you might want to look elsewhere.
faceoff_positive.headline: Does the job

faceoff_negative.comments:
I may have just picked the wrong color because th3 app I receieved this prodict from didn't show photos of what color each Buttermelt Highlighter was... Because I would NOT have chosen this color. The highlighter is a lilac color and VERY glittery. I prefer a more "pearl" type of finish for my highlighters so that they give a glow from within type of payoff...  This was also a little chunky and may take some trial and error to get it to work the way I usually like my highlighters to look. 

With that said - IT'S MARDI GRAS SEASON! So I will get great use out of this for the carnival season. But otherwise, I don't see myself using this except when wearing a costume.
